 'SHITHOLE COUNTRIES: In January 2018, Trump asked why the US would accept immigrants from "shithole countries "referring to Haiti, El Salvador, and African nations, expressing preference for Norwegian immigrants. The racial contempt underlying this statement reflects attitudes shaping policy toward non-white nations.',
 'HAITI EXPLOITATION PATTERN: Trump\'s history with Haiti includes alleged exploitation of Haitian labor. His administration ended Temporary Protected Status for Haitians despite continued humanitarian crisis. Policies forced people to return to extreme poverty and instability while corporations continued extracting cheap labor.',
 'IMF/WORLD BANK STRUCTURAL ADJUSTMENT: American-dominated international financial institutions impose "structural adjustment "conditions that require developing nations to cut social spending, privatize public assets, and open markets to foreign corporations. These policies benefit Western capital while impoverishing local populations.',
 'RESOURCE EXTRACTION: American corporations extract oil, minerals, and agricultural products from developing nations, often leaving environmental destruction and minimal local benefit. Tax structures, sweetheart deals, and corruption enable resource transfer to wealthy nations.',
 'TRADE AGREEMENT COERCION: The Trump administration used tariff threats and trade pressure to coerce developing nations into agreements benefiting American corporations. Threats to Guatemala, Honduras, and El Salvador on immigration tied aid to enforcement serving US interests.',
 'PHARMACEUTICAL IP: American trade policy forces developing nations to respect pharmaceutical patents, preventing production of affordable generic medications. This intellectual property regime privileges corporate profits over lives in poor countries.',
 'LABOR EXPLOITATION: Global supply chains exploit workers in developing nations, paying poverty wages in dangerous conditions to produce goods for American consumers. Corporate responsibility is minimized through subcontracting and complex ownership structures.',
 'DEBT BONDAGE: Developing nation debt to American banks and institutions creates ongoing transfer of wealth from poor to rich countries. Debt service payments exceed aid flows, perpetuating dependency.',
 'CLIMATE COLONIALISM: While developing nations bear the brunt of climate change impacts caused primarily by wealthy nations\' emissions, American policy has blocked climate reparations and technology transfer. Those least responsible suffer most.',
 'AGRICULTURAL DUMPING: Subsidized American agricultural products dumped on developing markets undercut local farmers, destroying rural livelihoods and creating food dependency. This benefits American agribusiness while impoverishing subsistence farmers.',
